<module status="bronze">
    <h>rionnag</h>
    <p><g>rionnag</g>
        <en>star</en> is a feminine derived common noun, with diminutive suffix <a href="?gd=_ag"
                ><g>-ag</g></a>.</p>
    <section>
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>The principal parts of <g>rionnag</g> are – <ul>
                <li><m>rionnag</m> – nominative singular</li>
                <li><m>rionnaige</m> – genitive singular</li>
                <li><m>rionnagan</m> – plural</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <section id="definiteness">
            <h>definiteness</h>
            <p><ul>
                    <li>indefinite <ul>
                            <li>singular <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>rionnag</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – (le) <m>rionnaig</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – (leabhar) <m>rionnaige</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>plural <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>rionnagan</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – (le) <m>rionnagan</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – (leabhar) <m>rionnagan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>definite <ul>
                            <li>singular <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>an rionnag</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – (leis) <m>an rionnaig</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – (leabhar) <m>na rionnaige</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>plural <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>na rionnagan</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – (leis) <m>na rionnagan</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – (leabhar) <m>nan rionnagan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                </ul></p>
        </section>
