    </section>
    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <module status="bronze" id="deps-spr-earball">
                <h>rionnag an earbaill</h>
                <p><g>rionnag an <a href="?gd=earball">earbaill</a></g>
                    <en>shooting star</en>, cf. Mark td. 487.</p>
            </module>
        </section>
        <section id="mods">
            <h>modifiers</h>
            <p>Idiom – <g>Chan eil fhios a(ga)m bho na rionnagan ruadha.</g> <en>I haven’t the faintest idea.</en> cf. Angus Watson (2001: 309)</p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <module status="bronze" id="uses-spr-lan">
                <h>làn rionnagan</h>
                <p><g><a href="?gd=làn">làn</a> rionnagan</g>
                    <en>starry</en>, cf. Mark td. 487.</p>
            </module>
        </section>
        <section id="uses-comp">
            <h>complement</h>
            <p>Idiom – <g>Chan eil fhios a(ga)m bho na rionnagan ruadha.</g> <en>I haven’t the faintest idea.</en> cf. Angus Watson (2001: 309)</p>
        </section>
        <section id="uses-deriv">
            <h>derivatives</h>
            <module status="bronze" id="uses-deriv-rionnagach">
                <h>rionnagach</h>
                <p><g>rionnagach</g>
                    <en>starry</en> is a derived adjective, with suffix <a href="?gd=_ach"
                            ><g>-ach</g></a>.</p>
                <section>
                    <h>uses</h>
                    <section>
                        <h>modifier</h>
                        <module status="bronze" id="uses-deriv-rionnagach-uses-mod-oidhche">
                            <h>oidhche rionnagach</h>
                            <p><g>air <a href="?gd=oidhche">oidhche</a> rionnagach</g>
                                <en>on a starry night</en>, cf. Mark td. 487.</p>
                        </module>
                    </section>
                </section>
            </module>
        </section>
    </section>


